			<ns0:name>pdox%goo...@gtempaccount.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/104735739662288482898/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Signed underflow/overflow is undefined behavior in C. So this is technically not a bug, but a feature. 

GCC optimization levels -O2 and above also assume -fstrict-overflow, which means they optimize aggressively assuming that signed over/under flow never happen.
